  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Uganda - Open Society</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Uganda Open Society is a one-year, &#xA3;0.25mn project that is aimed to deliver FCDO&#x2019;s ambition for an open society in Uganda. It will seek to a) experiment and build influential evidence, data and learning, to understand the best ways to achieve an open society in Uganda by 2026; b) address the lack of youth engagement to ensure their participation in decision-making in democratic governance processes and increase their voice in service delivery; and c) strengthen issue-based dialogue between the targeted citizens and those in power.</narrative>
  </description>
